1. *Pričao* sam s njim juče. (I talked to him yesterday.)
2. Ona *priča* najlepše priče. (She tells the most beautiful stories.)
3. Moram ti *pričati* nešto važno. (I have to tell you something important.)
4. Da li ti se *priča* o tome? (Do you feel like talking about it?)
5. Ne mogu *pričati* s tobom dok si tako besan. (I can't talk to you while you're so angry.)
6. Pusti me da *pričam* svoju priču. (Let me tell my story.)
7. Nisam siguran kako da *pričam* o ovome. (I'm not sure how to talk about this.)
8. *Pričaj* mi o svom putovanju. (Tell me about your trip.)
9. Hoću da mi *pričaš* o svojim snovima. (I want you to tell me about your dreams.)
10. Mama mi je uvek govorila da ne *pričam* s nepoznatima. (My mom always told me not to talk to strangers.)

Note: The word "priči" can have multiple meanings in Serbian, including "to talk," "to tell," "to narrate," and "to chat." The translations provided here reflect the context of each sentence.